  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nIf you turn off network connection and send emoji reaction right after - it won't be delivered when connection turned on. This is because in `status-go` we do not wait for acknowledgements from non-mailserver peers and automatically treat them as delivered. Same thing happens with chat messages - they treated as delivered while in reality they aren't\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nReaction resends when devices goes back online\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nReaction not resends when devices goes back online\r\n\r\n#### Notes\r\n\r\nRelated to #11020\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- turn off network connection and quickly add emoji reaction to any message\r\n- at this moment reaction can't be seen on other device\r\n- turn on network connection\r\n- make sure reaction seen on other device after short period of time\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n- Status version: 1.8\r\n- Operating System: Android,iOS",
